  "prompt": "What is Kargil war?",
  "response": "The Kargil War, also known as the Kargil Conflict, was an armed conflict between India and Pakistan that took place between May and July 1999 in the Kargil district of Jammu and Kashmir. It was sparked by the infiltration of Pakistani soldiers and militants into Indian territory. The Pakistani forces occupied strategic positions on the Indian side of the Line of Control (LoC), which divides the Indian-administered and Pakistani-administered parts of Kashmir.\n\nThe conflict began with India discovering the incursions and then launching Operation Vijay to evict the infiltrators. The fighting primarily took place in high-altitude areas with challenging terrain, making the military operations particularly difficult. The conflict included artillery exchanges, infantry battles, and airstrikes.\n\nThe war ended with India regaining control of the territories initially occupied by Pakistani forces. The conflict resulted in significant casualties on both sides and heightened tensions between the two neighboring countries. The Kargil War brought international attention to the ongoing disputes in Kashmir and strained relations between India and Pakistan.",
